  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nThe debugger relies on return statuses in receipts; however, these didn't exist prior to the Byzantium hardfork.\r\n\r\nI don't know to what extent we really want to do anything about this, but I thought I'd at least write this down.\r\n\r\n(It is worth noting that Byzantium is also the hardfork that introduced the `REVERT` opcode, i.e., the ability to revert with data; so to some extent the return status may not matter as much prior to Byzantium...?  I mean, obviously it matters, but...)\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.5.19",
